<h2>Form</h2>

<p>This library includes modules related to the form user interface element:</p>

<ul class="modules">
    <li><%= DOC.modules.render('Entity/Form') %></li>
</ul>

<p><span class="badge warning">WARNING</span> Examples here do not include all attributes that should be assigned to form controls, but rather only those to showcase the module. Attributes like <code>name</code>, <code>value</code>, etc. of course should also be included in real-world cases.</p>

<h3>Basic Form</h3>

<p>A basic form requires two components:</p>

<ul>
    <li><code>.form</code> class applied to the <code>form</code> element</li>
    <li>Each label/input group wrapped in a <code>div.control</code></li>
</ul>

<pre class="prettyprint">&lt;form class="form"&gt;
    &lt;div class="control"&gt;
        &lt;label for="i-1-1"&gt;Label 1&lt;/label&gt;
        &lt;input id="i-1-1"&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="control"&gt;
        &lt;label for="i-1-2"&gt;Label 1&lt;/label&gt;
        &lt;textarea id="i-1-2"&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="control"&gt;
        &lt;label for="i-1-3"&gt;Label 3&lt;/label&gt;
        &lt;select id="i-1-3"&gt;
            &lt;option&gt;Select Option 1&lt;/option&gt;
            &lt;option&gt;Select Option 2&lt;/option&gt;
        &lt;/select&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="control"&gt;
        &lt;input type="submit" class="button"&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;</pre>

<form class="form">
    <div class="control">
        <label for="i-1-1">Label 1</label>
        <input type="text" id="i-1-1">
    </div>
    <div class="control">
        <label for="i-1-2">Label 2</label>
        <textarea id="i-1-2"></textarea>
    </div>
    <div class="control">
        <label for="i-1-3">Label 3</label>
        <select id="i-1-3">
            <option>Select Option 1</option>
            <option>Select Option 2</option>
        </select>
    </div>
    <div class="control">
        <input type="submit" class="button">
    </div>
</form>

<h4>Help Text</h4>

<p>Any form control may include help text. If this help text is wrapped in a <code>p</code> tag, it will be displayed above/below the form input (depending), whereas if it simply follows the input such as in a <code>span</code> tag, then it will be display inline. It should be noted that this leverages the <code>aria-describedby</code> tag on the form control to reference the help text.</p>

<pre class="prettyprint">&lt;form class="form"&gt;
    &lt;div class="control"&gt;
        &lt;label for="i-2-1"&gt;Label 1&lt;/label&gt;
        &lt;p id="i-2-1-h"&gt;Help text above control&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;input id="i-2-1" aria-describedby="i-2-1-h"&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="control"&gt;
        &lt;label for="i-2-2"&gt;Label 2&lt;/label&gt;
        &lt;textarea id="i-2-2" aria-describedby="i-2-2-h"&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;
        &lt;span id="i-2-2-h"&gt;help text inline with control&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="control"&gt;
        &lt;label for="i-2-3"&gt;Label 3&lt;/label&gt;
        &lt;select id="i-2-3" aria-describedby="i-2-3-h"&gt;
            &lt;option&gt;Select Option 1&lt;/option&gt;
            &lt;option&gt;Select Option 2&lt;/option&gt;
        &lt;/select&gt;
        &lt;p id="i-2-3-h"&gt;Help text below control&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="control"&gt;
        &lt;input type="submit" class="button"&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;</pre>

<form class="form">
