<h4>Checkbox and Radio Button Support</h4>

<p>Checkboxes and radio buttons present a challenge in the case of accessibility because they may be labeled by two elements, namely one describing the "set" they belong to and then another describing that particular box. This module thus defines a particular markup style for them:</p>

<pre class="prettyprint">&lt;form class="form"&gt;
    &lt;div class="control"&gt;
        &lt;label id="i-4"&gt;Label&lt;/label&gt;
        &lt;label&gt;
            &lt;input type="checkbox" aria-labelledby="i-4"&gt; 
            description of first checkbox
        &lt;/label&gt;
        &lt;label&gt;
            &lt;input type="checkbox" aria-labelledby="i-4"&gt; 
            description for second checkbox
        &lt;/label&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="control"&gt;
        &lt;input type="submit" class="button"&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;</pre>

<form class="form">
    <div class="control">
        <label id="i-4">Label</label>
        <label>
            <input type="checkbox" aria-labelledby="i-4"> 
            first checkbox
        </label>
        <label>
            <input type="checkbox" aria-labelledby="i-4"> 
            second checkbox
        </label>
    </div>
    <div class="control">
        <input type="submit" class="button">
    </div>
</form>

<p>In some cases, one may wish to align a set of checkboxes or radio buttons inline rather than one per line. This can be accomplished by wrapping the set of checkboxes or radio buttons in a <code>div.inline</code>:</p>

<pre class="prettyprint">&lt;form class="form"&gt;
    &lt;div class="control"&gt;
        &lt;label id="i-5"&gt;Label&lt;/label&gt;
        &lt;div class="inline"&gt;
            &lt;label&gt;
                &lt;input type="radio" aria-labelledby="i-5"&gt; 
                first radio
            &lt;/label&gt;
            &lt;label&gt;
                &lt;input type="radio" aria-labelledby="i-5"&gt; 
                second radio
            &lt;/label&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="control"&gt;
        &lt;input type="submit" class="button"&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;</pre>

<form class="form">
    <div class="control">
        <label id="i-5">Label</label>
